### Description

I've recently noticed a case where the query parameters in the URL and the query parameters given by Angular diverge whenever using the navigate method and passing an empty array to a query parameter after it first had a "correct" value, and I'm not sure if this is intended behaviour or not.

a simple reproduction would be this
```ts
this.route.queryParams.subscribe((queryParams) => {
  console.log('queryParams', queryParams);
});

this.router.navigate([], {
  queryParams: {
    countries: [1, 2, 3],
  },
}).then(() => {
  this.router.navigate([], {
    queryParams: {
      countries: [],
    },
  });
});
```

upon navigating, the URL wouldn't have any query parameters, however, the log would give out `{ countries: [] }`.

